Random Forest 
Random Forest is a supervised machine learning algorithm used for both classification and regression problems. It is an ensemble learning method, meaning it combines the predictions of multiple Decision Trees to improve accuracy and reduce overfitting. Instead of relying on a single tree, Random Forest creates many trees using random samples of the training data and combines their predictions. For classification problems, the final prediction is obtained through majority voting, while for regression problems, it uses the average of all predictions.

